metadata.name: Matter Waves #170
metadata.description:
If light, which is generally a wave, can also sometimes be a particle - then can matter also be a wave? Louis De Broglie suggested this idea, which is supported by performing a double slit experiment with matter particles and producing an interference pattern that indicates wave behaviour. Performing the experiment with one particle at a time also produces an interference pattern, implying the particles create interference with themselves. One way this could be possible is if the particle travels infinite potential paths simultaneously, super positioning itself in many places at once. If one electron can be in infinite places at once, is it possible that all electrons are that same one? More than thinking everything is connected, can we go one further and think that everything is the same thing? 

'Matter Waves' super positions connections between constellated nodes, spreading them out through space in multiple ways - an aesthetic exploration of these ideas. 

's' to save large file
'1' to watch it load slowly 
'2' to watch it load super slowly

Fully live code in p5js

@amygoodchild

metadata.name: Candles #250
metadata.description:
Why are you into NFT's? Chasing the profit or loving the art? The "Candles" project arises from this dilemma.

Once you mint, the market will open and randomly decide whether you win or lose. 
There is Dark and Light Mode and very rarely you will mint a Single Loop Trader Mode piece, which is by far the dullest version, and at the same time the rarest and so the most valuable... 
So question yourself, would I rather mint a dull and valuable piece, or a colorful piece of art to enjoy.

And oh, If you press "r" you will be able to see your profit (or loss) and toggle it on/off. just for fun :-)

@Elum0x, pure Javascript, Brussels 2022.

metadata.name: Voyage #40
metadata.description:
"Voyage" was created from a dream I had where all forms of water accumulation looked alike, the sea, lakes, swamps and pools all had their visuals matched, becoming just a fountain.

With this concept, every form of water has become something calm and peaceful, where we can contemplate and calm down.

Made with p5.js and chroma.js
This piece adapts to your window size

Press "S" to save a screenshot on your computer :)

metadata.name: AutomataPunk, The Masquerader #493
metadata.description:
A playful spin on PFPs, and the prevalence of them on social media, especially among the NFT community.
The characters are procedurally generated, and then colored and texturized using 1D Cellular Automata.
Masqueraders hide their rarity scores. The cutest or most unusual one will be the most popular.
Their dimensions are always a multiple of 360.

Controls:
- Press 's' to save a PNG file.
- Press 't' to toggle, for a larger and higher resolution version that once complete can be saved as a 3600x3600 PNG by pressing 's'. In this mode, the Masquerader may become much larger than your screen. Wait for its render to complete before saving it. Toggle back to the regular size by pressing 't' again.

License:
See included LICENSE.md

Credits:
Made in p5js

By default the dimensions of the export are 3200√ó2400.
